Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
analyze_paths_by_hierarchy(25.10)            analyze_paths_by_hierarchy(25.10)

Name
       analyze_paths_by_hierarchy  - Creates categories according to the hier-
       archical characteristics of the paths

Syntax
       analyze_paths_by_hierarchy

       [-help]

       [-master <string>]

       {-fp_file <string> [-include_macros ]} | {-use_current_floorplan  [-all
       ]   [-types  <string>]  [-port2port  ]  [-port2macro  ]  [-port2bbox  ]
       [-port2hinst  ]  [-port2stdcell  ]  [-port2instgrp  ]  [-macro2port   ]
       [-macro2macro  ]  [-macro2bbox  ]  [-macro2hinst  ]  [-macro2stdcell  ]
       [-macro2instgrp  ]  [-bbox2port  ]   [-bbox2macro   ]   [-bbox2bbox   ]
       [-bbox2hinst   ]  [-bbox2stdcell  ]  [-bbox2instgrp  ]  [-hinst2port  ]
       [-hinst2macro  ]  [-hinst2bbox  ]  [-hinst2hinst  ]  [-hinst2stdcell  ]
       [-hinst2instgrp  ]  [-stdcell2port ] [-stdcell2macro ] [-stdcell2bbox ]
       [-stdcell2hinst  ]  [-stdcell2stdcell  ]  [-stdcell2instgrp  ]  [-inst-
       grp2port ] [-instgrp2macro ] [-instgrp2bbox ] [-instgrp2hinst ] [-inst-
       grp2stdcell  ]  [-instgrp2instgrp  ]} | {-partitions <string> | -macros
       <string>}

       Creates categories according to the hierarchical characteristics of the
       paths. User can use either a user specified floorplan file  or  current
       floorplan  file  of  the design in memory and can create categories ac-
       cording to the hierarchy of the design. This way, the paths can be nar-
       rowed down to small group.

Use Floorplan Plan:
       The software automatically extracts partition-boundary information from
       guides, regions, and fences in the floorplan file. Optionally  you  can
       specify option to sort paths based on the macros in the floorplan file.

              * All paths fully contained in a single partition, Ptn1.

              * Paths  starting  in one partition and ending in another parti-
                tion, Ptn1->Ptn2.

              * Paths spanning several partitions, Ptn1-> Ptn2->Ptn3.

              * Top-level inputs to partitions, INPUT->Ptn1.

              * Paths from partitions to top-level outputs, Ptn1->OUTPUT.

Use Current Floorplan:
       This method categorizes paths based on the current floorplan of the de-
       sign in memory. It will rely on the grouped/ungrouped as  a  basis  for
       what  level to view the hierarchy as well as what levels to create tim-
       ing categories .

       Grouped/ungrouped status of an Hinst means whether or not its  children
       are shown on the floorplan view.

       It  categorizes  paths starting and ending on/within these hierarchical
       entities:

              * Port

              * Hard Macro (ungrouped)

              * Black Box (ungrouped)

              * Hinst (regular, partition, Black Blob, or Flex Model) (highest
                grouped)

              * Stdcell (ungrouped)

       For more information on creating path categories,  see  "Creating  Path
       Categories" in the Debugging Timing Results chapter of User Guide.

Parameters
       -all   Creates categories of paths within all types

              Default: All types are categorized.

       -bbox2instgrp
              Creates categories of paths from black box to instance group.

              Type: Bool, optional

       -bbox2port
              Creates categories of paths from black box to port.

       -bbox2macro
              Creates categories of paths from black box to macro.

       -bbox2bbox
              Creates categories of paths from black box to black box.

       -bbox2hinst
              Creates  categories  of paths from black box to hierarchical in-
              stance.

       -bbox2stdcell
              Creates categories of paths from black box to standard cell.

       -fp_file floorplan_file
              Specifies the name of the floorplan file.

              Default: Uses the current floorplan file.

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each analyze_paths_by_hierarchy parameter.

              For  a  detailed  description of the command and all its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man analyze_paths_by_hierarchy

       -hinst2port
              Creates categories of paths from hierarchical instance to port.

       -hinst2macro
              Creates categories of paths from hierarchical instance to macro.

       -hinst2bbox
              Creates categories of paths from hierarchical instance to  black
              box.

       -hinst2hinst
              Creates  categories of paths from hierarchical instance to hier-
              archical.

       -hinst2instgrp
              Creates categories of paths from hierarchical  instance  to  in-
              stance group.

              Type: Bool, optional

       -hinst2stdcell
              Creates  categories of paths from hierarchical instance to stan-
              dard cell.

       -include_macros
              Includes macros in addition to guides and  fences  for  creating
              categories.

              Default: Macros are not considered.

       -instgrp2bbox
              Creates categories of paths from instance group to black box.

              Type: Bool, optional

       -instgrp2hinst
              Creates  categories of paths from instance group to hierarchical
              instance.

              Type: Bool, optional

       -instgrp2instgrp
              Creates categories of paths  from  instance  group  to  instance
              group.

              Type: Bool, optional

       -instgrp2macro
              Creates categories of paths from instance group to macro.

              Type: Bool, optional

       -instgrp2port
              Creates categories of paths from instance group to port.

              Type: Bool, optional

       -instgrp2stdcell
              Creates  categories  of  paths  from  instance group to standard
              cell.

              Type: Bool, optional

       -macros <macro_list>
              Specifies the names of the macros to be used. Use this parameter
              with the -partitions parameter.

       -macro2instgrp
              Creates categories of paths from macro to instance group.

              Type: Bool, optional

       -master <master_category_name>
              Specifies that the timing paths should be categorized  only  for
              the specified master category.

       -partitions <partition_list>
              Specifies the names of the partitions to consider for extracting
              hierarchical information.

       -port2instgrp
              Creates categories of paths from port to instance group.

              Type: Bool, optional

       -port2port
              Creates categories of paths from port to port.

       -port2macro
              Creates categories of paths from port to macro.

       -port2bbox
              Creates categories of paths from port to black box.

       -port2hinst
              Creates categories of paths from port to hierarchical instance.

       -port2stdcell
              Creates categories of paths from port to standard cell.

       -macro2port
              Creates categories of paths from macro to port.

       -macro2macro
              Creates categories of paths from macro to macro.

       -macro2bbox
              Creates categories of paths from macro to black box.

       -macro2hinst
              Creates categories of paths from macro to hierarchical instance.

       -macro2stdcell
              Creates categories of paths from macro to standard cell.

       -stdcell2port
              Creates categories of paths from standard cell to port.

       -stdcell2macro
              Creates categories of paths from standard cell to macro.

       -stdcell2bbox
              Creates categories of paths from standard cell to black box.

       -stdcell2hinst
              Creates  categories  of paths from standard cell to hierarchical
              instance.

       -stdcell2instgrp
              Creates categories of  paths  from  standard  cell  to  instance
              group.

              Type: Bool, optional

       -stdcell2stdcell
              Creates categories of paths from standard cell to standard cell.

       -types type_list
              Creates categories of paths within the type_list.

              Valid types are: port, macro, bbox, hinst, stdcell

       -use_current_floorplan
              Uses the current floorplan.

Examples:
              *
                 By default, it categorizes all the paths inter/intra in the 5
                hierarchical entities by following command :

                analyze_paths_by_hierarchy -use_current_floorplan -all

              *
                 The following command categorizes all paths from "port" or to
                "port":

                analyze_paths_by_hierarchy -use_current_floorplan -type port

Related Information
       The Timing Budgeting chapter of the Innovus User Guide document.

